# Engram Dual License

Engram is available under two licensing options:

## 1. MIT License (Community Use)

For **individuals, educational institutions, and community projects**, Engram is licensed under the MIT License. See [LICENSE-MIT](LICENSE-MIT) for full terms.

**Permitted uses under MIT:**
- Personal projects
- Educational and research purposes
- Open-source projects
- Non-commercial applications

## 2. Commercial License

For **organizations using Engram in commercial products, services, or platforms**, a commercial license is required.

**Commercial use includes:**
- Integration into proprietary software or SaaS products
- Use in revenue-generating applications or services
- Deployment in commercial platforms or infrastructure
- White-labeling or reselling Engram functionality

**To obtain a commercial license:**

Contact: license@foundation42.org
Organization: Foundation42
Website: https://github.com/Foundation42

## How to Choose

If you're unsure which license applies to your use case:

- **MIT License:** If you're an individual developer, student, researcher, or working on an open-source project
- **Commercial License:** If your organization generates revenue from products or services that use Engram

When in doubt, reach out to license@foundation42.org for clarification.

